# Archive

<!--
  BL-089: the archive convention, scaffolded at project birth as
  docs/archive/README.md. Archiving WITHOUT stubs manufactures ghost
  citations — the convention's load-bearing half.
-->

Superseded working documents live here. Two rules, both mandatory:

1. **Move with a status banner.** When a document is superseded, MOVE it into
   this directory and add a one-line banner at its top: what superseded it,
   and when (`> **SUPERSEDED** by docs/<new-path> — YYYY-MM-DD`).
2. **Leave a pointer stub at the old path.** The old path keeps a short stub
   file pointing here, so every existing citation still resolves. Deleting
   the old path instead of stubbing it turns every reference to it into a
   ghost citation.

Ledgers (APPROVAL_LOG.md, CHANGELOG.md, BUGS.md) are never archived.
APPROVAL_LOG and CHANGELOG are append-only records; BUGS.md appends rows and
updates each row's status cells in place (its inline format contract —
gate-parsed). None are working documents. See `docs/INDEX.md` for the ledger
vs living-document distinction and the authority order.
